message.content: Iris foetidissima, also known as the stinking iris, is a plant species belonging to the Iridaceae family. It is a perennial, evergreen plant that grows up to 70cm tall. The leaves are long and narrow, with a rough texture and a bluish-green color. It produces flowers that are small and purple, with yellow and white markings. The fruit of the Iris foetidissima is a large, oblong capsule that contains bright orange-red berries. This plant is native to Western Europe and can be found growing in woodlands, hedgerows, and limestone cliffs. Despite its unpleasant odor, the Iris foetidissima has some medicinal properties and is used in traditional medicine to treat various ailments.
